{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "lxxe:psalms.48",
    "translationId": "lxxe",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 48,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 48 in Brenton's English Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.1",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:1",
      "text": "For the end, a Psalm for the sons of Core. - Hear these words, all ye nations, hearken, all ye that dwell upon the earth:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.2",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:2",
      "text": "both the sons of mean men, and sons of great men; the rich and poor man together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.3",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:3",
      "text": "My mouth shall speak of wisdom; and the meditation of my heart shall bring forth understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.4",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:4",
      "text": "I will incline mine ear to a parable: I will open my riddle on the harp.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.5",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:5",
      "text": "Wherefore should I fear in the evil day? the iniquity of my heel shall compass me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.6",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:6",
      "text": "They that trust in their strength, and boast themselves in the multitude of their wealth—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.7",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:7",
      "text": "A brother does not redeem, shall a man redeem? he shall not give to God a ransom for himself,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.8",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:8",
      "text": "or the price of the redemption of his soul, though he labour for ever,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.9",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:9",
      "text": "and live to the end, so that he should not see corruption.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.10",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:10",
      "text": "When he shall see wise men dying, the fool and the senseless one shall perish together; and they shall leave their wealth to strangers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.11",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:11",
      "text": "And their sepulchres are their houses for ever, even their tabernacles to all generations: they have called their lands after their own names.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.12",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:12",
      "text": "And man being in honour, understands not: he is compared to the senseless cattle, and is like to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.13",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:13",
      "text": "This their way is an offence to them: yet afterwards men will commend their sayings. Pause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.14",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:14",
      "text": "They have laid them as sheep in Hades; death shall feed on them; and the upright shall have dominion over them in the morning, and their help shall fail in Hades from their glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.15",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:15",
      "text": "But God shall deliver my soul from the power of Hades, when he shall receive me. Pause.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.16",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:16",
      "text": "Fear not when a man is enriched, and when the glory of his house is increased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.17",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:17",
      "text": "For he shall take nothing when he dies; neither shall his glory descend with him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.18",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:18",
      "text": "For his soul shall be blessed in his life: he shall give thanks to thee when thou dost well to him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.19",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:19",
      "text": "Yet he shall go in to the generation of his fathers; he shall never see light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "lxxe:psalms.48.20",
      "translationId": "lxxe",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:20",
      "text": "Man that is in honour, understands not: he is compared to the senseless cattle, and is like them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
